üìò Experiment ‚Äì 04 : Jenkins Installation and Setup
AIM
To install Jenkins, perform initial setup, and explore the Jenkins environment for automation tasks.

OBJECTIVE

Install Java (JDK 11 or higher)

Install Jenkins on the system

Unlock Jenkins and configure admin user

Install suggested plugins

Explore Jenkins dashboard

Run a sample freestyle project to verify installation

SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS

Java JDK 11 or higher

Jenkins package (jenkins.war or system installation)

Web browser

üöÄ LAB PROCEDURE
1. Install Java (If not installed)
java -version

Windows installation steps (based on PDF):

Search for "JDK download"
Open Oracle website
Download JDK 21 x64 Installer
Install with default settings
Verify Java:
java -version
2. Install Jenkins
Windows installation (from PDF)
Search ‚ÄúJenkins download‚Äù
Open first link (jenkins.io)
Download Java Generic Package (.war)
Open Command Prompt
Navigate to the folder containing jenkins.war
Run:
java -jar jenkins.war


This starts Jenkins on http://localhost:8080

4. Retrieve Jenkins Initial Admin Password

After installation, Jenkins generates an initial password.

Windows
It appears in the command prompt when Jenkins starts from jenkins.war.
Copy this password.

5. Access Jenkins Web Interface

Open browser ‚Üí

http://localhost:8080
6. Unlock Jenkins

Paste the initialAdminPassword into the setup wizard to continue.

7. Install Suggested Plugins

Choose:

‚úî Install Suggested Plugins

According to the screenshots on page 4, plugins include:

Git

Pipeline

Workspace Cleanup

Credentials Binding

SSH Build Agents

Timestamper

GitHub Branch Source

LDAP
‚Ä¶and more.

Wait until installation completes.
8. Create First Admin User

Fill in:

Username

Password

Full Name

Email Address

Then continue to dashboard.
9. Explore Jenkins Dashboard

You will see options such as:

New Item

Manage Jenkins

Build History

Credentials

Explore the interface and settings.

10. Verify Jenkins Installation
‚úî Create a freestyle project

Click New Item

Choose Freestyle Project

Add a simple build step (e.g., print message)

Run the build

If the build succeeds ‚Üí Jenkins is installed correctly.
